[normal]Clearly, this was a very difficult day for both transport operators and would-be passengers, but I believe East Coast did all it reasonably could help people with their journeys.   It is also relevant, I 
[normal]think, that from the evening of 27
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]October onwards, information  had  been  published for  prospective passengers about the cancellation of rail services, advising them to avoid travelling if possible on 28 October, so that the number of people on the 
[normal]move was substantially lower than normal.
